        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 4:20PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 420 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Goat Rock Lake, or
near Smiths, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Pine Mountain, Waverly Hall, Bibb City, Goat Rock Lake,
Ellerslie, Laurel Hills, Green Island Hills, Cataula, Mountain Hill,
Fortson, Pine Mountain Valley, Mulberry Grove, and Lake Harding.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
